I've got an issue that's kept me from brewing for the past few months, and it's really getting to be obnoxious.After moving into my girlfriend's rental home, I kept my bubbling fermenters in her closet, as it provided plenty of space and insulation. Unfortunately, this area was also available to her 4-year old daughter, who ended up ruining 3 different batches by depositing crayons, rocks, coins, and whatever she could fit into the carboy.Needless to say, using the closet is no longer an option.I've thought about getting a chest freezer & temp controller (or build some kind of fermentation chamber) to keep in the garage. Unfortunately, the one outlet actually in the garage doesn't work, and the landlord isn't interested in repairing it. There's an outlet in the laundry room right next to the garage, but that involves running an extension cord and having the door constantly closing on it.No brewing makes me a sad hamster. Big Wooly Mammoth
